-- Xoom says could post adj 3rd-quarter loss, shares tumble
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Tue Jul 22, 2014 05:03PM EDT
-- None



July 22 (Reuters) - Money transfer company Xoom Corp <XOOM.O> said it could post an adjusted loss in the third quarter, sending its shares down 13 percent after the bell.

On an adjusted basis, the company expects net results to range between a loss of 1 cent and a profit of 2 cents per share on revenue of $39 million to $41 million. [ID:nGNXVBBRDa]